data.title: GoPro Music: Matt and Kim “Let’s Run Away” BTS
data.description:
Inspired by Nicolas Vuignier’s Centriphone technique, Matt built his own homemade bullet-time rig. This time, a little more durable, with a GoPro. 
Explore Matt’s simple but elegant setup and dive into a look behind the scenes of Matt and Kim’s incredibly vibrant and innovative music video for “Let’s Run Away”. 

Matt and Kim's new music video, "Let's Run Away"

WE WERE THE WEIRDOS 

Shot 100% on the HERO4® camera

Music
Matt and Kim
"Let's Run Away" Instrumental

data.title: GoPro Music: Matt and Kim’s GoPro Catapults Into Crowd at Governors Ball 2016
data.description:
For Matt and Kim’s latest music video, they used a wooden coat hanger, some fishing wire, and a GoPro filming 720p at 240 frames per second. The result: a circular moment frozen in time. Watch them take the rig to the stage at Governors Ball 2016 with a little help from Curt from Flosstradamus. The wire didn’t hold up and we get an up-close and personal look at the NYC crowd! 

Shot 100% on the HERO4® camera 

MUSIC:
Matt and Kim - "Please No More" 
from the new EP - WE WERE THE WEIRDOS 

Matt and Kim's new music video, "Let's Run Away", shot in the same style

WE WERE THE WEIRDOS

data.title: GoPro: 61 Wingsuiters Fly Together – A World Record
data.description:
After weeks of practice on the ground, Matthew Barrientos and 60 of his closest anti-gravity-companions took to the skies to break the record for the largest predetermined formation wingsuit flight. Jumping out of four different planes over Perris, California, watch as the record-breaking formation of 61 people comes together at sunset!

Special thanks to Matthew Barrientos and Taya Weiss for filming this incredible jump! 

Shot 100% on the HERO4® camera 

Music
Odesza “All We Need (Dawn Golden remix)”
